@startuml State_Transfer
title Fund Transfer - State Diagram

skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor<<success>> #90EE90
    BackgroundColor<<failure>> #FFB6C1
}

[*] --> Scheduled

Scheduled : Transfer created and\nqueued for execution
Scheduled --> Initiated : scheduledDateReached\n/ call Plaid API

Initiated : Plaid transfer request\nsubmitted successfully
Initiated --> Processing : plaidWebhook(posted)
Initiated --> Failed <<failure>> : plaidWebhook(failed)\n[retryCount >= 3]
Initiated --> Scheduled : plaidWebhook(failed)\n[retryCount < 3] / retry

Processing : ACH transfer in progress\nat banking network
Processing --> Completed <<success>> : plaidWebhook(settled)
Processing --> Failed <<failure>> : plaidWebhook(returned)\n[retryCount >= 3]
Processing --> Scheduled : plaidWebhook(returned)\n[retryCount < 3] / retry

Completed <<success>> : Funds received at\ndestination account
Completed --> [*]

Failed <<failure>> : Transfer permanently\nfailed after retries
Failed --> [*]

note right of Scheduled
  Retry uses exponential
  backoff: 1, 2, 4 days
end note

note right of Completed
  On completion:
  - Update savings ledger
  - Notify user
  - Log for audit
end note

@enduml
